{"SkeletonMage_TitlePage":{"!ObjectScript":"res://assets/Scripts/Items/Pages/PageItemTitle.gd","!ParentKey":"#BaseTitlePage","#ObjDetails":{"Description":"Due to @@#Color:Red:Mages'@@ innate lack of muscle tissue, it's inevitable they will become a @@#Color:Red:Skeleton@@ if turned @@#Tag:Undead@@. Less inevitable, however, is if they can retain their @@#Tag:Spell:Hint:Spell Pages@@ and the @@#Stat:Intelligence@@ required to use them.\n\nTheir bare bones body has the same resistances and vulnerabilities any other @@#Color:Red:Skeleton@@, but their @@#Color:Red:Dark Robes@@ provide @@#Stat:Ward@@ and a sense of modisty.\n\n@@#Color:Red:Skeleton Mages@@ are known to be aggressive front-line @@#Tag:Melee@@ fighters relying on high defense and just kidding, they cast @@#Tag:Spell:Hint:Spells@@ from a safe distance.","DisplayName":"Skeleton Mage","LargeIcon":"Sprites/SkeletonMageTitle_Icon.png","ObjectType":"Item","SmallIcon":"Sprites/SkeletonMageTitle_Icon.png","SnippetDesc":"Skeleton Mage Title","Tags":["Title"],"Taxonomy":["Item","Page","Title"]},"ItemData":{"ItemType":"Page","Rarity":"Unique","Value":50.0},"PageData":{"AddTags":["Undead","Skeleton","Mage"],"PageRequirements":{"ConflictingPages":[],"IncompatiblePages":[],"TitleReq":"None"},"SourceTitle":"Base","StatMods":{"MagAttackScale":{"DepStatName":"Intelligence","DisplayName":"Base Stats","ModType":"AddStat","StatName":"MagAttack","Value":1.0}}},"PassiveData":{},"_DefVersion":"1"},"Skeleton_TitlePage":{"!ObjectScript":"res://assets/Scripts/Items/Pages/PageItemTitle.gd","!ParentKey":"#BaseTitlePage","#ObjDetails":{"Description":"A spooky scary @@#Color:Red:Skeleton@@ risen from the dead. This form of reanimation accounts for a lack of muscle tissue by directly manipulating bones. The resulting @@#Tag:Undead@@ is physically weaker, but has the @@#Stat:Agility@@ required to use @@#Tag:Ranged:Hint:Ranged Weapons@@.\n\nThier exposed bone is resistant to @@#Color:DmgColor:Slash@@ and @@#Color:DmgColor:Pierce@@, but is quite vulnerable to @@#Color:DmgColor:Blunt@@ and @@#Color:DmgColor:Crash@@. They often remain on back lines using range to attack from afar.\n\nWhile some may view them as nightmarish monsters, I like to believe there's a @@#Color:Red:Skeleton@@ inside us all.","DisplayName":"Skeleton","LargeIcon":"Sprites/SkeletonTitle_Icon.png","ObjectType":"Item","SmallIcon":"Sprites/SkeletonTitle_Icon.png","SnippetDesc":"Skeleton Title","Tags":["Title"],"Taxonomy":["Item","Page","Title"]},"ItemData":{"ItemType":"Page","Rarity":"Unique","Value":50.0},"PageData":{"AddTags":["Undead","Skeleton"],"PageRequirements":{"ConflictingPages":[],"IncompatiblePages":[],"TitleReq":"None"},"SourceTitle":"Base","StatMods":{}},"PassiveData":{},"_DefVersion":"1"},"Zombie_TitlePage":{"!ObjectScript":"res://assets/Scripts/Items/Pages/PageItemTitle.gd","!ParentKey":"#BaseTitlePage","#ObjDetails":{"Description":"@@#Color:Red:Zombies@@ are a common form of @@#Tag:Undead@@ created through the reanimation of a @@#Color:Red:Corpse@@. They are peaceful beings almost never resorting to violence, except towards all @@#Tag:Living@@ creatures whom they relentlessly attack on sight.\n\nBasic @@#Color:Red:Zombies@@ are @@#Tag:Unarmed@@ and mostly rely on weak punches. But when they're feeling feisty, they can steal @@#Stat:Health@@ with a @@#Color:Red:Bite Attack@@. Paired with their high @@#Stat:HealthMax@@ they can make for effective meat shields.\n\n@@#Color:Red:Zombies@@ have an innate love of helicopters, gleefully chasing after any they see fly by. Sadly, no one ever lets them ride in one.","DisplayName":"Zombie","LargeIcon":"Sprites/ZombieTitle_Icon.png","ObjectType":"Item","SmallIcon":"Sprites/ZombieTitle_Icon.png","SnippetDesc":"Zombie Title","Tags":["Title"],"Taxonomy":["Item","Page","Title"]},"ItemData":{"ItemType":"Page","Rarity":"Unique","Value":50.0},"PageData":{"AddTags":["Undead","Zombie"],"PageRequirements":{"ConflictingPages":[],"IncompatiblePages":[],"TitleReq":"None"},"SourceTitle":"Base","StatMods":{}},"PassiveData":{},"_DefVersion":"1"}}